# Before Committing
Always run `mise run check` from the mono root. It runs checks based on changed files vs dev branch.

# Quick Reference - Common Check Commands
```bash
# Full check (runs relevant checks based on git diff)
mise run check

# Run all checks regardless of diff
mise run check --all

# Static checks only (skip pytest/hurl)
mise run check --static
```

# Python Checks (core, api, microservices)

## Ruff Linting & Formatting
- Line length: 88 characters
- Auto-fix enabled - ruff will fix most issues automatically
- Key rules enforced:
  - `F401` - Remove unused imports
  - `I` - isort import sorting
  - `T20` - No print statements (except in scripts)
  - `S101` - No assert in production code (allowed in tests)
  - `D101-D103, D417` - Google-style docstrings required
  - `UP` - Modern Python syntax (pyupgrade)
  - `PLC0415` - Imports must be at module level, not inside functions

```bash
mise run api:ruff       # Lint API
mise run api:format     # Format API
mise run core:ruff
mise run core:ruff_format
```

## Type Checking (mypy)
- Python 3.12 target
- SQLAlchemy plugin enabled
- All functions should have type hints
- `disallow_untyped_defs = false` (gradual typing)

```bash
mise run api:types
mise run core:types
```

## Semgrep Rules
- `star-syntax` - Functions must use `*` for keyword-only args (except routes)
- `sqlalchemy-query-filter` - No `.query()` or `.filter()` - use `select()` + `.where()`
- `with-async-db` - Don't use `_with_async_db` directly in routes

```bash
mise run api:star_syntax
mise run api:sqlalchemy
```

## Dead Code & Unused Imports
- Vulture (min-confidence 100) - finds unused code
- Deptry - finds unused dependencies

```bash
mise run api:vulture
mise run api:deptry
```

## Unused Routes Check
- `check_unused_routes.py` detects API endpoints not used in web-app or other code
- **Do NOT** add routes to `ALLOWED_UNUSED_ROUTES` if they are actually used in web-app
- Instead, ensure frontend hooks use the exact route path in `axiosConfig.url` so the script can detect usage
- Only add to `ALLOWED_UNUSED_ROUTES` for legitimately unused internal/background endpoints

## Docstrings
- All public functions need docstrings with Args section
- Google docstring convention

```bash
mise run api:docstring_args
mise run core:docstring_args
```

# TypeScript/React Checks (web-app)

```bash
mise run web:check    # TypeScript + Prettier + Knip
mise run web:lint     # oxlint only
```

## Other Web Checks
- No `console.log` in source files
- Knip checks for unused exports/dependencies

# Common Failure Modes & Fixes

| Check | Common Issue | Fix |
|-------|-------------|-----|
| `star_syntax` | Missing `*` in function params | Add `*` after first positional arg |
| `sqlalchemy` | Using `.filter()` | Replace with `.where()` |
| `docstring_args` | Missing Args in docstring | Add Google-style Args section |
| `vulture` | Unused function | Remove or add to whitelist if false positive |
| `ruff F401` | Unused import | Remove the import |
| `ruff PLC0415` | Import inside function | Move import to top of file |
| `check_unused_routes` | Route in ALLOWED list | Update frontend hook to use exact route path |

# Package-Specific Commands

## Core
```bash
mise run core:check       # All core checks
mise run core:db "msg"    # Generate migration
mise run core:release     # Full release workflow
```

## API
```bash
mise run api:check        # All API checks
mise run api:run          # Run dev server
mise run api:pytest       # Run tests
```

## Web-App
```bash
mise run web:check        # TS + Prettier + Knip
mise run web:dev          # Dev server
mise run web:build        # Production build
```

# Codegen
After changing API schemas or enums, regenerate TypeScript types:
```bash
mise run codegen
```
